abstract: U.S. stocks have entered a new bull market, and the S&P 500 index could rise as much as 10 percent from current levels by the end of this year, Goldman Sachs strategist Abby Joseph Cohen said on CNBC on Thursday.
snippet: U.S. stocks have entered a new bull market, and the S&P 500 index could rise as much as 10 percent from current levels by the end of this year, Goldman Sachs strategist Abby Joseph Cohen said on CNBC on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: U.S. stocks have entered a new bull market, and the S&P 500 index could rise as much as 10 percent by Dec. 31, Abby Joseph Cohen, equities strategist at Goldman Sachs said on CNBC on Thursday.

headline.main: Goldman’s Cohen Says New Bull Market Has Begun
